[{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/SimGus/Chatette/issues/comments/559610230","html_url":"https://github.com/SimGus/Chatette/issues/30#issuecomment-559610230","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/SimGus/Chatette/issues/30","id":559610230,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDU1OTYxMDIzMA==","user":{"login":"SimGus","id":20604236,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIwNjA0MjM2","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/20604236?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/SimGus","html_url":"https://github.com/SimGus","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SimGus/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SimGus/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SimGus/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SimGus/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SimGus/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SimGus/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SimGus/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SimGus/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SimGus/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2019-11-28T22:03:57Z","updated_at":"2019-11-28T22:03:57Z","author_association":"OWNER","body":"Hi,\r\n\r\nNesting slots is not a supported feature, because it is not clear what the generated sentence should look like. To me, using the templates you showed, the slot `@[paymentPeriod]` should generate something like this: `[[hour](paymentPeriod:hour)](paymentPeriod)`. As you may know, this is not supported by Rasa.\r\nTo avoid having this kind of problems, I will add an error if Chatette detects nested slots in your templates.\r\n\r\nNow, seeing your template, I think I understand what you want to be generated: you would like a slot called `paymentPeriod` that could contain either `hour`, `h`, `day` or `d`, is that right?\r\nIf so, the following template will achieve this:\r\n```\r\n~[paymentPeriod:hour]\r\n\thour\r\n\th\r\n~[paymentPeriod:day]\r\n\tday\r\n\td\r\n\r\n@[paymentPeriod]\r\n        ~[paymentPeriod:hour]\r\n        ~[paymentPeriod:day]\r\n```\r\n\r\nOn the other hand, if you want a slot called `paymentPeriod:hour` that could have the values `hour` or `h` and another one called `paymentPeriod:day` that could have the values `day` or `d`, then I'm afraid you will have to make 2 different slots and use them wherever you want, as in the following template:\r\n```\r\n@[paymentPeriod:hour]\r\n\thour\r\n\th\r\n@[paymentPeriod:day]\r\n\tday\r\n\td\r\n\r\n~[some alias]\r\n        ... [@[paymentPeriod:hour]|@[paymentPeriod:day]] ...\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf what you're looking for is some kind of \"categories of slots\" (e.g. `hour` and `day` being 2 slots that are part of a `paymentPeriod` category), I am afraid Rasa doesn't support this kind of things. Therefore, Chatette doesn't support it neither. That being said, I might add something like this in the far future, but I'll need to find a solution to \"translate\" them to something Rasa would understand.\r\n\r\nHope this helps!","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/SimGus/Chatette/issues/comments/559610230/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"SimGus","id":20604236,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIwNjA0MjM2","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/20604236?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/SimGus","html_url":"https://github.com/SimGus","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SimGus/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SimGus/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SimGus/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SimGus/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SimGus/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users